    <fr:title text="morphism of ringed spaces">morphism of ringed spaces</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  Given two <fr:link href="/forest/algm-000M/" title="ringed space" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/algm-000M/" display-uri="algm-000M" type="local">ringed spaces</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X, Y]]></fr:tex>, a morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi  : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> is given by a continuous map of the underlying spaces, and a sheaf morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi ^{-1} \mathscr {O}_Y \to  \mathscr {O}_X]]></fr:tex>, equivalently <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {O}_Y \to  \varphi _* \mathscr {O}_X]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
